                <h1>Discovering the Roots of Chipotle: A Journey Through Its History</h1>
                <p>Chipotle Mexican Grill was founded in 1993 by Steve Ells in Denver, Colorado. Initially a small burrito joint, its emphasis on fresh, high-quality ingredients and sustainability soon captured the public's attention. By 2006, Chipotle had expanded rapidly, forging a reputation as a leader in fast-casual dining with its customizable menu.</p>
